---
title: Herby Beef Burgers with Potato Wedges and Tomato Salad
description: There are few things more delicious than a perfectly juicy homemade burger. Especially when they’re on the table in 40 minutes flat. Served alongside chunky potato wedges and a chimichurri tomato salad for a kick of heat, it’s hard to go wrong with this super simple recipe. To avoid a saucer-shaped patty, make a slight indentation with your thumb in the centre of your raw patty. This helps the meat cook evenly, maintaining its shape as it shrinks during cooking.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/herby-burgers-11e94636-5730d07a.jpg
